  "_exec_summary": [
    {
      "ESSeqNum": 0,
      "FacilityID": 1000096322,
      "SummaryText": "As a joint venture of Corning Inc, and Shin-Etsu Handotai, Hemlock Semiconductor subscribes to and fully supports the American Chemistry Council (ACC) Responsible Care (RC)initiative and the RC 14001 management standard.  Voluntarily participating in these programs is a part of our commitment to improve environmental, health, safety and sustainability performance.\n\n\n\nThe Hemlock, Michigan manufacturing facility has implemented a Risk Management Plan. The facility maintains communication with the local community officials through its Community Advisory Panel (CAP) and other activities.\n\n\n\nAccidental release prevention and emergency response policies\n\nHemlock Semiconductor uses policies and procedures to manage environmental, health, and safety performance. The company has established a Code of Business Conduct to guide its employees. In addition, the Hemlock facility has implemented safety and environmental management systems.\n\n\n\nFacility overview and regulated substances\n\nThe Hemlock, Michigan facility manufactures ultra-pure silicon based materials for use by electronic device and solar cell manufacturers. The following RMP-regulated chemicals are used in the manufacturing processes:\n\n   Hydrogen Chloride\n\n   Dichlorosilane\n\n   Trichlorosilane\n\n   Flammable mixtures containing varying amounts of Dichlorosilane, Trichlorosilane, and Hydrogen\n\n\n\nAccident prevention program\n\nThe facility uses a systematic approach to prevent accidental releases through employee and contractor programs that include; training, preventive maintenance, policies, procedures, safety reviews, change management procedures, investigations and compliance audits.\n\n\n\nIn addition, the facility has implemented chemical-specific accident prevention measures, including:\n\n   Automated emergency shutdown systems\n\n   Use of nitrogen to inert storage tanks\n\n   Use of high-performance, corrosion-resistant materials\n\n   Continuous air monitoring at select locations\n\n   Infrared camera/detection at select l"
    },
    {
      "ESSeqNum": 1,
      "FacilityID": 1000096322,
      "SummaryText": "ocations \n\n   Emergency hydrogen chloride scrubbers\n\n\n\nFive-year accident history\n\nThe facility has had no RMP-reportable accidents in the previous five years.  \n\n\n\nEmergency response program\n\nThe Hemlock Facility uses an Incident Command (IC) system for emergency planning and response activities. The system is based on the National Incident Management System (NIMS) model, modified to fit the facilities organization and operations. Emergency response plans are coordinated with the Saginaw County Local Emergency Planning Committee and various Saginaw County Emergency Response Agencies, including the Thomas Township Fire Department. The facility conducts periodic drills to train site and community emergency response personnel, and participates in community-wide drills. The facility maintains an emergency phone line to provide important information and current plant status during any community emergency. \n\n\n\nThe emergency response program includes the following:\n\n   Dedicated Loss Prevention personnel that are trained in emergency response and help monitor/maintain the site's life safety systems\n\n   130-plus production employees trained as Specialist Employees to assist with emergencies in their respective areas\n\n   Fixed fire protection, including sprinklers, fire monitors and hydrants\n\n   Dedicated emergency response vehicles:\n\n      Two Industrial Fire Apparatus\n\n      Hazmat/Heavy Rescue\n\n      Emergency Response Trailers \n\n      Two State qualified Basic Life Support Vehicles\n\n      Various high flow vapor mitigation tools\n\n\n\nPlanned changes to improve safety\n\nHemlock Semiconductor strives to continuously improve its environmental, health, safety and sustainability performance through process changes, management system and equipment reliability improvements. The facility uses a formalized, project-oriented approach to improve performance in conjunction with routine hazard assessments and audits.  \n\n"
    }
  ]
